(Memory consolidation research has repeatedly highlighted sleep as an active biological context) Tj
0 -14 Td
(in which newly encoded representations are reorganized, stabilized, and made more retrievable.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Rather than a period of neural inactivity, sleep involves coordinated oscillatory events that) Tj
0 -14 Td
(appear to facilitate communication between hippocampal and neocortical systems. The) Tj
0 -14 Td
(contemporary systems consolidation account proposes that recently formed episodic traces are) Tj
0 -14 Td
(initially hippocampus dependent and subsequently reorganized through offline replay and) Tj
0 -14 Td
(cortical integration. In practical terms, this framework predicts better delayed recall) Tj
0 -14 Td
(following sleep than following matched intervals of wakefulness, especially for tasks requiring) Tj
0 -14 Td
(declarative retrieval.) Tj
0 -14 Td
() Tj
0 -14 Td
(Parallel to this sleep-consolidation literature, targeted memory reactivation has emerged as a) Tj
0 -14 Td
(method for experimentally probing memory replay. In typical paradigms, participants learn) Tj
0 -14 Td
(material paired with sensory cues \(often sounds or odors\), and a subset of those cues is) Tj
0 -14 Td
(replayed later, usually during non-rapid eye movement sleep or during quiet wake. If the cue) Tj
0 -14 Td
(successfully reactivates associated traces, retention can improve relative to uncued items or) Tj
0 -14 Td
(control conditions. TMR therefore functions both as a mechanistic probe and as a potential) Tj
0 -14 Td
(intervention framework. Importantly, not all cueing is beneficial: effects depend on timing,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(cue salience, sleep stage, and the quality of initial encoding.) Tj
0 -14 Td
